**Briefs Community Overview:**
- **Event Title:** COM - Briefs Community
- **Description:** A platform for sharing brief talks (10 minutes or less) on various topics within the security domain. Presenters can discuss projects, successes, and failures while sharing learned insights with peers.
- **Organizers:** G0vn4571 and Sheeprock

**Presentation Details:**
- **Format:** Short talks that are casual and informal.
- **Presentation Requirements:** 
  - Presenters need only an idea and a willingness to stand in front of an audience. 
  - A small slide show is encouraged to accompany the talk.
  
**Sign-Up Information:**
- Interested presenters can sign up via [this link](https://forms.gle/76Ex5bDKfhoic4RE9).

**Hours of Operation:**
- **Monday:** Expo Closed
- **Tuesday:** During Lunch
- **Wednesday:** During Lunch
- **Thursday:** During Lunch
- **Friday:** No Briefs

**Additional Community Offerings:**
- **MiniBadge:** Available for participants. Details can be inquired during briefs, with potential unique badges for presenters.

**Community Goals:**
- Foster engagement and conversation among peers.
- Allow skill refinement in short topic presentation formats.

**Downloadable Content:**
- Desktop wallpaper related to the community is available for download.

**Further Information:**
- **Community Links:**
  - Discord: [Join us on Discord](https://discord.gg/saintcon)
  - MiniBadge Specifications: [GitHub Link](https://github.com/lukejenkins/minibadge)
- **Previous Events:** Links to past events from SAINTCON 15 to SAINTCON 23 are provided for reference.

**Website:** [SAINTCON](https://saintcon.org)